The Bronx woman who was killed in an early morning altercation with her ex-boyfriend had a restraining order against him for months.

20-year-old Katherine German was killed Wednesday morning when her stalker ex-boyfriend Doines Espinal witnessed her leaving a motel with another man.

He followed German and her new boyfriend Jose Jimenez and repeatedly rammed their car until it hit a concrete barrier and flipped over.

